    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the slide pins and they seem to move okay. the squeal is super sharp though, almost like metal on metal. could it be that the wear indicator is hitting the rotor? i'm worried i might have messed something up during the install.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sharp, metal-on-metal squeal after a brake job sounds like something a little more serious than just a simple sticking pin, though don't panic yet. If it sounds like metal scraping metal, you need to look closely at the rotor and the pads. It could absolutely be the wear indicator—that little metal tab designed to tell you when the pads are thin—making contact with the rotor. It's a very common, albeit annoying, thing, especially if the pads weren't seated perfectly flush.",
      "source": "target",
